{"name":"DMG12 App. C: Maps","folder":"MjfHAFZjhTrOmXNO","sort":1200028,"flags":{"srd5e":{"source":"DMG","entryIds":["3af"]}},"_id":"AXolPUOcLCSMCUdt","pages":[{"name":"DMG12 App. C: Maps","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div class=\"w-100 h-100 overflow-x-hidden\"><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--0\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--0\" data-title-index=\"2151\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Appendix C: Maps</span><span class=\"ve-flex-vh-center\"> <span class=\"rd__title-link \">p310</span><span class=\"rd__h-toggle ml-2 clickable\" data-rd-h-toggle-button=\"true\">[–]</span></span></span> <p>Creating a map for an adventure is a fun, challenging, and time-consuming endeavor. However, unless you have something specific in mind, you're better off conserving your time and energy by repurposing an existing map. Published adventures and the Internet are terrific sources for maps. A few sample maps are included here as well. Use them as you will!</p><div class=\"rd__wrp-gallery\"><p></p><div class=\"float-clear\"></div><div class=\"rd__wrp-gallery-image\"><div class=\"rd__wrp-image relative\">\n\t\t\t<a href=\"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/book/DMG/app-c-1.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n\t\t\t\t<img class=\"rd__image\" src=\"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/book/DMG/app-c-1.jpg\" />\n\t\t\t</a>\n\t\t</div></div><p></p><p></p><div class=\"float-clear\"></div><div class=\"rd__wrp-gallery-image\"><div class=\"rd__wrp-image relative\">\n\t\t\t<a href=\"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/book/DMG/app-c-2.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n\t\t\t\t<img class=\"rd__image\" src=\"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/book/DMG/app-c-2.jpg\" />\n\t\t\t</a>\n\t\t</div></div><p></p><p></p><div class=\"float-clear\"></div><div class=\"rd__wrp-gallery-image\"><div class=\"rd__wrp-image relative\">\n\t\t\t<a href=\"https://5etools-mirror-1.github.io/img/book/DMG/app-c-3.jpg\" target=\"_